AI-generated code is untrusted until validated.
No push to main.
Required flow is: branch -> commit -> CI -> review -> human approval -> merge.
Task completion requires a Git checkpoint on the active feature branch.
Default /git behavior must not merge main implicitly.
CI is authoritative.
No raw conversation logs in long-term memory.
No direct agent-to-agent calls.
Scheduler must validate task ownership and task status transitions before dispatch or state mutation.
Dead-letter repeated failures and require human attention after retry exhaustion.
